  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best books of body language?",
  "response": "There are several highly-regarded books on body language that offer valuable insights into non-verbal communication. Here are some of the best:\n\n1. **\"The Definitive Book of Body Language\"** by Allan and Barbara Pease\n   - This book provides a comprehensive overview of body language, combining research and practical examples to illustrate how non-verbal cues influence communication.\n\n2. **\"What Every BODY is Saying: An Ex-FBI Agent's Guide to Mastering the Art of Body Language\"** by Joe Navarro\n   - Written by a former FBI agent, this book delves into the signals people give off and how to interpret them accurately in various situations.\n\n3. **\"The Body Language Bible\"** by Lillian Glass\n   - This book covers a wide range of body language topics, focusing on how to read and respond to others' non-verbal communication.\n\n4. **\"You Can't Lie to Me: The Revolutionary Program to Trust Your Instincts\"** by Janine Driver and Mariska Hargitay\n   - This book combines body language interpretation with emotional cues, emphasizing how to trust your instincts when reading others.\n\n5. **\"The Like Switch: An Ex-FBI Agent's Guide to Influencing, Attracting, and Winning People Over\"** by Jack Schafer and Marvin Karlins\n   - While primarily focused on building rapport and influence, this book incorporates body language strategies that can help improve social interactions.\n\n6. **\"Body Language for Dummies\"** by Elizabeth Kuhnke\n   - This beginner-friendly guide covers the basics of body language and provides practical applications for everyday situations.\n\n7. **\"The Power of Body Language\"** by Tonya Reiman\n   - This book explores how body language can be utilized in various environments, from personal relationships to professional settings, emphasizing the impact of non-verbal communication.\n\n8. **\"Emotions Revealed: Recognizing Faces and Feelings to Improve Communication and Emotional Life\"** by Paul Ekman\n   - Although not exclusively about body language, this book offers insights into emotional expressions and how they relate to non-verbal cues.\n\nThese books provide a solid foundation for understanding body language and enhancing your communication skills.",
